WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:05.005
-[OPENING THEME PLAYS]

00:12.708 --> 00:15.667
-♪ SOME PEOPLE STAND
IN THE DARKNESS ♪

00:16.886 --> 00:20.368
♪ AFRAID TO STEP
INTO THE LIGHT ♪

00:20.933 --> 00:24.328
♪ SOME PEOPLE NEED
TO HELP SOMEBODY ♪

00:24.459 --> 00:27.766
♪ WHEN THE END OF
SURRENDER'S IN SIGHT ♪

00:27.897 --> 00:30.595
♪ DON'T YOU WORRY

00:31.335 --> 00:33.685
♪ IT'S GONNA
BE ALL RIGHT ♪

00:36.732 --> 00:38.516
♪ 'CAUSE I'M ALWAYS READY

00:38.647 --> 00:42.259
♪ I WON'T LET YOU
OUT OF MY SIGHT ♪

00:45.393 --> 00:49.136
♪ I'LL BE READY,
I'LL BE READY ♪

00:49.266 --> 00:53.270
♪ NEVER YOU FEAR,
NO, DON'T YOU FEAR ♪

00:53.401 --> 00:55.968
♪ I'LL BE READY

00:56.665 --> 00:59.233
♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS

00:59.885 --> 01:02.062
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE

01:20.863 --> 01:22.865
♪ 'CAUSE I'M ALWAYS READY

01:22.995 --> 01:26.042
♪ I WON'T LET YOU
OUT OF MY SIGHT ♪

01:29.480 --> 01:33.354
♪ I'LL BE READY,
I'LL BE READY ♪

01:33.484 --> 01:37.358
♪ NEVER YOU FEAR,
NO, DON'T YOU FEAR ♪

01:37.488 --> 01:40.100
♪ I'LL BE READY

01:40.752 --> 01:43.407
♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS

01:43.973 --> 01:46.802
♪ I'M ALWAYS HERE ♪

02:15.091 --> 02:16.223
-YOUR PRESCRIPTION
WILL BE READY

02:16.353 --> 02:17.137
IN JUST A MINUTE,
MR. O'HARA.

02:17.267 --> 02:18.790
-THANKS, SAM, NO HURRY.

02:18.921 --> 02:21.358
I HAVE TO PICK OUT A
BIRTHDAY CARD, ANYWAY.

02:22.751 --> 02:24.405
-THIS IS EXPIRING,
MISS CAPSHAW,

02:25.145 --> 02:26.668
AND MAKE SURE YOU TAKE
THOSE PILLS WITH FOOD.

02:26.798 --> 02:28.191
THEY'RE VERY POWERFUL.

02:28.322 --> 02:30.019
-I PROBABLY WON'T
EVEN NEED THESE.

02:30.150 --> 02:31.542
IT'S JUST IN CASE.

02:31.673 --> 02:33.414
-OKAY, IT'LL BE JUST
A COUPLE OF MINUTES.

02:33.544 --> 02:34.415
-THANKS.

02:45.687 --> 02:47.950
-GIVE ME THE CASH
IN THE REGISTER. NOW!

02:48.080 --> 02:49.604
BACK OFF! BACK OFF!

02:49.734 --> 02:51.736
STAY OVER
THERE, OLD MAN!

02:56.872 --> 02:58.917
GET UP!
GET UP!

03:00.745 --> 03:01.833
GIVE ME THE CASH.

03:04.619 --> 03:06.186
-I THINK HE'S HAVING
A HEART ATTACK.

03:10.102 --> 03:11.234
CALL 9-1-1, HURRY!

03:17.240 --> 03:18.981
-YES, WE HAVE AN
EMERGENCY RIGHT NOW!

03:19.111 --> 03:20.112
A MAN IS HAVING A
HEART ATTACK!

03:20.765 --> 03:22.027
YES, HE'S DOWN
RIGHT NOW.

03:22.767 --> 03:27.555
-ONE, TWO, THREE, FOUR,
FIVE, SIX, SEVEN, EIGHT --

03:27.685 --> 03:29.296
-NO, HE'S GETTING CPR.

03:30.253 --> 03:31.950
-NEELY: TWELVE, THIRTEEN,
FOURTEEN, FIFTEEN.

03:35.127 --> 03:36.999
FIVE, SIX, SEVEN, EIGHT.

03:37.129 --> 03:38.783
-NEWS ANCHOR: THE ROBBER
IS STILL AT LARGE.

03:39.393 --> 03:41.786
THE VICTIM, JOHN O'HARA, TRULY
HAD THE LUCK OF THE IRISH

03:41.917 --> 03:43.310
WITH HIM YESTERDAY.

03:43.440 --> 03:44.615
HE SUFFERED HIS HEART
ATTACK RIGHT NEXT

03:44.746 --> 03:45.921
TO AN OFF-DUTY LIFEGUARD.

03:46.443 --> 03:49.533
NEELY CAPSHAW FROM BAYWATCH
INSTANTLY BEGAN CPR.

03:49.664 --> 03:50.926
WHEN THE PARAMEDICS ARRIVED,

03:51.056 --> 03:52.884
THE QUICK-ACTING
CAPSHAW HAD SUCCESSFULLY

03:53.015 --> 03:55.844
RESTORED O'HARA'S PULSE,
SAVING THE MAN'S LIFE.

03:56.627 --> 03:58.281
HE'S STABLE NOW AND
RESTING COMFORTABLY

03:58.412 --> 03:59.674
AT ST. JOHN'S HOSPITAL.

03:59.804 --> 04:01.763
-THERE IT IS.
[LAUGHTER AND APPLAUSE]

04:01.893 --> 04:03.765
LET'S SUBMIT HER FOR
A MEDAL OF VALOR.

04:04.331 --> 04:05.288
-DONNA: HEY,
WHEN'S SHE COMING IN?

04:05.419 --> 04:06.289
-MITCH: THIS AFTERNOON.

04:06.420 --> 04:07.812
-DONNA: I'VE MISSED HER.

04:07.943 --> 04:09.553
THE SKIING ACCIDENT
WAS PRETTY BAD, HUH?

04:09.684 --> 04:11.686
-EVIDENTLY, SHE HAD A
HERNIATED DISC IN HER BACK,

04:11.816 --> 04:13.165
TRACTION, THE WHOLE WORKS.

04:13.296 --> 04:14.689
-THINK SHE'S
READY TO LIFEGUARD?

04:14.819 --> 04:15.864
-I KNOW SHE'S GONNA
NEED SOMEONE TO HELP

04:15.994 --> 04:16.995
HER GET IN SHAPE
FOR THE RECHECK.

05:33.898 --> 05:35.073
-OH, MY BACK.

05:35.204 --> 05:36.640
-DONNA: NEELY,
ARE YOU OKAY?

05:38.250 --> 05:39.121
-YEAH, I'M FINE.

05:39.643 --> 05:40.427
-DONNA: ARE YOU SURE?

05:41.079 --> 05:41.993
-OKAY, THANKS.

05:42.516 --> 05:43.691
-DONNA: DO YOU
THINK YOU CAN JOG?

05:44.648 --> 05:45.475
-SURE.

05:52.961 --> 05:53.962
-YOU'RE SURE
YOU'RE ALL RIGHT?

05:54.092 --> 05:55.180
-I'M FINE.

06:28.997 --> 06:29.867
-HMM.

06:41.139 --> 06:43.011
EXCUSE ME, WHAT ARE
YOU GUYS DOING HERE?

06:47.624 --> 06:48.843
-YOU DON'T WANNA KNOW.

06:48.973 --> 06:49.974
-I NEED TO KNOW.

06:58.113 --> 06:59.157
-THAT IS MY UNCLE.

06:59.984 --> 07:01.769
HE SAYS IT'S TIME
FOR HIM TO DIE.

07:03.248 --> 07:05.425
-DIE? WHEN?

07:06.513 --> 07:07.688
-HE SAYS SOON.

07:09.254 --> 07:10.038
-HERE?

07:10.168 --> 07:11.648
-I'M AFRAID SO.

07:11.779 --> 07:14.521
-[LAUGHS] HE CAN'T DIE HERE.

07:14.651 --> 07:16.305
THIS IS A PUBLIC BEACH.

07:16.958 --> 07:17.959
-NOT ANY MORE.

07:20.135 --> 07:21.528
-DON'T LET HIM
DO ANYTHING.

07:21.658 --> 07:24.226
JUST MAKE SURE HE STAYS
ALIVE UNTIL I GET BACK.

07:25.836 --> 07:30.101
-[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

07:57.172 --> 08:00.958
-[TRIBAL MUSIC]

08:25.548 --> 08:26.506
-HEY, WHAT'S GOING ON?

08:26.636 --> 08:28.290
-MITCH, THIS IS ANNA.

08:28.420 --> 08:29.639
-HI, ANNA.

08:30.335 --> 08:33.077
-LANI: AND THAT'S HER
UNCLE, EYES THAT SEE AT NIGHT.

08:33.730 --> 08:34.731
-WHAT'S HE DOING?

08:34.861 --> 08:35.993
-IT'S A CHUMASH
DEATH BED.

08:36.124 --> 08:36.951
-MITCH: WHAT?

08:37.604 --> 08:38.822
-A DEATH BED.

08:39.562 --> 08:41.346
HE HAS CHOSEN
THIS PLACE TO DIE.

08:42.826 --> 08:45.046
-MISS, IF YOUR
UNCLE IS SICK,

08:45.176 --> 08:47.875
MAYBE YOU SHOULD GET
HIM TO A HOSPITAL.

08:48.005 --> 08:50.530
-HE WAS IN THE HOSPITAL,
BUT HE LEFT TO COME HERE.

08:51.487 --> 08:54.490
LISTEN, I'M REALLY SORRY
FOR CAUSING A SCENE.

08:54.621 --> 08:57.275
MY UNCLE, HE'S
VERY OLD-FASHIONED,

08:57.406 --> 09:00.191
AND TRADITIONAL,
AND VERY STUBBORN.

09:00.322 --> 09:02.280
ONCE HE MAKES
UP HIS MIND--

09:03.804 --> 09:05.327
-WE'VE GOT A LITTLE
BIT OF A PROBLEM HERE.

09:05.457 --> 09:08.504
WE'RE L.A. COUNTY LIFEGUARDS,
AND THIS IS OUR BEACH.

09:08.635 --> 09:10.114
HE CANNOT DIE HERE.

09:10.245 --> 09:11.942
HE'S GONNA HAVE TO GO
BACK TO THE HOSPITAL.

09:13.117 --> 09:14.771
-WELL, HE SAYS
HE WON'T LEAVE.

09:15.685 --> 09:17.382
WE'RE WAITING FOR HIS
LAWYER TO GET HERE.

09:17.513 --> 09:19.689
-[LAUGHS] LOOK, I DON'T
THINK YOU WANNA GET

09:19.820 --> 09:21.386
INTO LEGAL ISSUES HERE.

09:21.517 --> 09:23.998
WE SHOULD BE ABLE TO RESOLVE
THIS BETWEEN OURSELVES.

09:24.955 --> 09:26.522
-LOOK, I'D LIKE
TO BE COOPERATIVE,

09:26.653 --> 09:28.132
BUT HE WON'T LEAVE

09:28.263 --> 09:29.960
NOW THAT HE'S STARTED HIS
JOURNEY DOWN THE PATH.

09:30.482 --> 09:31.745
-WHAT KIND OF PATH?

09:31.875 --> 09:34.269
-HIS FINAL PATH
FROM THIS WORLD.

09:36.140 --> 09:38.273
-ANNA: IF HE DOESN'T
ENTER THE PATH FROM HERE,

09:38.403 --> 09:40.057
THE LAND OF HIS ANCESTORS,

09:41.015 --> 09:43.191
HE BELIEVES HIS SPIRIT
WILL WANDER FOREVER.

09:45.062 --> 09:45.889
-EXCUSE ME.

09:52.287 --> 09:54.376
HI, MY NAME
IS MITCH BUCHANNON.

09:54.506 --> 09:55.856
I'M AN L.A.
COUNTY LIFEGUARD.

09:56.596 --> 09:58.119
I UNDERSTAND
WHAT YOU'RE DOING,

09:58.815 --> 10:02.427
BUT, SIR, YOUR PATH
CANNOT BE HERE.

10:02.558 --> 10:05.300
-IT IS HERE, AS
IT ALWAYS HAS BEEN.

10:05.909 --> 10:09.609
-I CAN'T STAND BY AND
LET YOU DIE ON THIS BEACH.

10:10.131 --> 10:11.480
IT'S NOTHING PERSONAL.

10:11.611 --> 10:13.525
IT'S AGAINST THE LAW.

10:13.656 --> 10:15.005
-WHITE MEN'S LAW MAYBE,

10:15.136 --> 10:16.703
BUT THAT'S SECONDARY
TO HIS TRIBAL LAW.

10:18.182 --> 10:19.967
-MITCH: [LAUGHS] CRAIG!

10:20.097 --> 10:22.056
-HEY, BUDDY, HOW ARE YOU?

10:22.186 --> 10:23.840
-WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

10:24.798 --> 10:25.668
-WELL,

10:29.890 --> 10:30.847
I'M HIS LAWYER.

10:31.674 --> 10:35.417
-[SOFT MUSIC]

10:40.030 --> 10:42.163
-[SOFT ROCK MUSIC]

10:45.645 --> 10:46.994
-BEST FOURTH OF JULY.

10:47.124 --> 10:49.997
-1990, NO, NO, NO, '91.

10:50.954 --> 10:53.957
-SKINNY DIPPING AND
FIREWORKS AT MALIBU PIER.

10:54.088 --> 10:56.394
-THEN HOT CRAB AND
COLD BEER AT POINT DUME.

10:56.525 --> 10:57.657
-AWESOME, AWESOME.

10:59.049 --> 11:01.791
-HEY, GUESS I MISSED YOU.

11:01.922 --> 11:04.228
I'M JUST CALLING TO
SEE HOW YOU'RE DOING.

11:04.359 --> 11:05.447
I'LL TRY LATER. BYE.

11:06.796 --> 11:07.928
-GINA'S NOT HOME?

11:08.058 --> 11:12.193
-UH UH. BEST
CATALINA TRIP.

11:14.108 --> 11:15.152
-BIG AL'S RENTAL BOAT.

11:15.283 --> 11:16.327
NO, NO, NO, NO, NO.

11:17.502 --> 11:19.374
THE LOBSTER DIVE. [LAUGHS]

11:19.504 --> 11:20.636
-IN THE POURING RAIN.

11:20.767 --> 11:22.594
-MITCH: IN THE
RAIN, AWESOME.

11:25.162 --> 11:26.686
YOU KNOW, I
GOTTA TELL YOU,

11:28.470 --> 11:29.732
I ADMIRE YOU FOR WHAT
YOU'RE DOING FOR THAT GUY,

11:29.863 --> 11:32.039
WHAT'S HIS NAME, EYES --

11:32.169 --> 11:33.301
-EYES THAT SEE AT NIGHT.

11:33.431 --> 11:34.911
-THAT'S COOL.

11:35.433 --> 11:36.347
-THANKS.

11:38.698 --> 11:41.265
SIX YEARS OF REDUCING
CORPORATE TAX LIABILITIES.

11:43.746 --> 11:45.879
IT'S NICE TO BE ABLE TO HELP
PEOPLE INSTEAD OF PORTFOLIOS.

11:47.097 --> 11:50.013
WHAT YOU DO, MAKING A
DIFFERENCE IN PEOPLE'S LIVES,

11:50.840 --> 11:52.624
THAT HAS MEANING.

11:52.755 --> 11:54.888
-IT MAY HAVE MADE A DIFFERENCE
TODAY, BUT JUST SO YOU KNOW,

11:55.018 --> 11:57.412
THE COUNTY IS GOING TO SEND
AN ATTORNEY OUT TOMORROW,

11:57.542 --> 11:59.022
AND THEY'RE GONNA MAKE
THAT OLD GUY LEAVE.

11:59.153 --> 12:00.067
-MAYBE.

12:00.937 --> 12:02.765
I'LL GET A COURT ORDER
AND HE'LL BE BACK.

12:03.810 --> 12:05.725
-WHAT IF THE GUY
DOESN'T DIE?

12:05.855 --> 12:10.425
I MEAN, HE COULD BE ON THE
BEACH FOR THE NEXT 10 YEARS.

12:11.034 --> 12:13.167
-MITCH, THE GUY'S
TERMINAL. HE'S GONNA DIE.

12:13.297 --> 12:15.038
I THINK HE'S GOT A RIGHT
TO DIE ON THAT BEACH,

12:15.169 --> 12:16.736
AND I JUST WANNA TRY
TO PROTECT THAT RIGHT.

12:19.956 --> 12:21.262
-NEELY: MITCH!
-DONNA: HEY!

12:21.871 --> 12:23.394
-HEY, HEY, COME HERE,
COME HERE, COME HERE.

12:24.004 --> 12:25.527
DONNA MARCO, NEELY CAPSHAW,

12:25.657 --> 12:27.181
I'D LIKE YOU TO
MEET CRAIG POMEROY.

12:27.311 --> 12:28.922
CRAIG IS AN OLD LIFEGUARD.

12:29.052 --> 12:30.401
-NOT THAT OLD.

12:30.532 --> 12:32.012
I'VE STILL GOT SOME
MILES LEFT ON ME.

12:32.142 --> 12:34.536
-ABSOLUTELY, I WOULDN'T
MIND TAKING A TEST DRIVE.

12:34.666 --> 12:35.842
-DONNA: NEELY.

12:35.972 --> 12:38.540
-SORRY, NEELY,
CRAIG IS MARRIED.

12:39.323 --> 12:40.498
-I DON'T SEE A RING.

12:42.892 --> 12:45.373
-SO, CRAIG, HOW LONG HAVE
YOU BEEN LIFEGUARDING?

12:45.503 --> 12:47.592
-DO YOU HAVE A TAN
LINE ON YOUR FINGER?

12:47.723 --> 12:49.029
OH!

12:49.986 --> 12:51.379
-HANG ON, HANG ON,
HANG ON, HERE YOU GO.

12:51.509 --> 12:52.423
HERE YOU GO.

12:53.773 --> 12:54.861
-CHEERS.

13:06.568 --> 13:07.438
-[LAUGHING]

13:07.961 --> 13:09.223
-MAN: ABSOLUTELY!

13:09.353 --> 13:10.485
-WOMAN: LOOKING GOOD!

13:10.615 --> 13:14.054
-[BEACH-GOERS CHATTER]

13:14.184 --> 13:15.403
-HEY, HOBIE, HOLD UP.

13:16.621 --> 13:18.275
HEY!

13:18.406 --> 13:19.799
I THINK WE SHOULD HEAD UP
TO CLUB RIO TONIGHT, MAN.

13:20.538 --> 13:21.844
IT'S THE HOTTEST CLUB
IN TOWN RIGHT NOW.

13:21.975 --> 13:23.150
-YEAH, MAN, IT'S
WALL-TO-WALL BABES.

13:23.280 --> 13:24.629
-COME WITH US, HOBE.

13:24.760 --> 13:26.980
-YEAH, MAN, I KNOW
ABOUT THE CLUB RIO, MAN.

13:27.110 --> 13:29.591
I ALSO KNOW YOU HAVE TO BE
21 TO GET IN THAT PLACE.

13:29.721 --> 13:31.332
-NO, NO, NO, YOU
HAVE TO HAVE AN ID

13:31.462 --> 13:33.464
THAT SAYS YOU'RE 21
TO GET IN THAT PLACE.

13:34.117 --> 13:34.944
-CHECK IT OUT.

13:39.253 --> 13:40.645
-WOW, MAN,
THAT LOOKS REAL.

13:40.776 --> 13:41.951
WHERE'D YOU GET IT?

13:42.082 --> 13:43.431
-I KNOW THIS GUY
WHO MAKES 'EM.

13:43.561 --> 13:44.911
THEY WORK EVERY TIME.

13:45.041 --> 13:46.521
-YEAH, MAN, ONLY 20
BUCKS AND YOU'RE IN.

13:46.651 --> 13:47.565
WHAT DO YOU SAY?

13:50.568 --> 13:52.179
-CRAIG: HEY,
THANKS FOR DINNER.

13:52.309 --> 13:53.571
YOU SURE YOU DON'T MIND ME
BUNKING HERE FOR A WHILE?

13:54.094 --> 13:56.270
-CRAIG, I GOT A
GUEST ROOM, RIGHT?

13:56.400 --> 13:58.359
YOU'RE A GUEST.
IT ALL WORKS.

13:58.968 --> 13:59.839
-THANKS.

14:01.318 --> 14:02.624
HOW ABOUT I USE YOUR
PHONE TO CALL GINA.

14:02.754 --> 14:04.191
-HELP YOURSELF.

14:04.321 --> 14:05.235
WHEN YOU GET HER, TELL
HER I SAID HI, WILL YOU?

14:05.366 --> 14:06.497
-CRAIG: YEP.

14:09.065 --> 14:10.806
HEY, IT'S ME AGAIN.

14:10.937 --> 14:14.288
JUST THOUGHT I'D CALL AND
SEE HOW YOU'RE DOING AND UH...

14:14.418 --> 14:16.377
OH, MITCH SAYS HI.

14:16.507 --> 14:17.334
IT'S THE MACHINE.

14:17.944 --> 14:19.336
-HEY, GINA!

14:19.467 --> 14:22.470
-CRAIG: I GUESS I'LL TRY
AGAIN SOMETIME TOMORROW.

14:23.384 --> 14:24.254
BYE.

14:26.343 --> 14:27.649
-WHERE IS SHE?

14:27.779 --> 14:29.912
-SHE'S OUT SOMEWHERE.
I DON'T KNOW.

14:30.043 --> 14:30.826
-[MUG THUDS AGAINST TABLE]

14:30.957 --> 14:32.175
THE MOVIES OR SOMETHING.

14:32.306 --> 14:33.655
-THE MOVIES?

14:34.743 --> 14:37.180
CRAIG, IT'S 3:00 IN THE
MORNING IN WASHINGTON.

14:40.009 --> 14:40.880
-YEAH.

14:42.098 --> 14:42.969
-[MITCH SIGHS]

14:48.888 --> 14:52.065
-ALL RIGHT,
WHAT'S GOING ON?

14:56.460 --> 15:00.160
-GINA AND I ARE,
UH, SEPARATED.

15:01.813 --> 15:04.381
-[SIGHS] OH, MAN, I'M
SORRY. I DIDN'T KNOW.

15:07.297 --> 15:08.211
HOW LONG?

15:08.342 --> 15:09.256
-THREE MONTHS NOW,

15:11.301 --> 15:13.347
WHICH EXPLAINS MY
RING-LESS TAN LINE.

15:16.089 --> 15:17.133
-WHAT HAPPENED?

15:17.264 --> 15:18.918
-IT'S THE SAME
OLD STORY.

15:20.267 --> 15:23.313
WHAT'S THE EXPRESSION?
GROWING APART.

15:23.879 --> 15:26.751
-YEAH, I KNOW THAT ONE.

15:27.274 --> 15:29.624
-GINA JUST LOVES THE WASHINGTON
SOCIAL LIFE, YOU KNOW.

15:29.754 --> 15:31.974
SHE GOT SUCKED INTO
IT MORE AND MORE,

15:32.105 --> 15:35.760
AND I JUST GOT TO A POINT
WHERE I COULDN'T STAND IT,

15:35.891 --> 15:36.936
OR MY JOB.

15:37.066 --> 15:38.415
IT'S EVERYTHING
BACK THERE.

15:38.546 --> 15:39.677
IT'S THE POLITICS, IT'S
THE BACK-STABBING.

15:41.114 --> 15:42.071
-DID YOU TRY COUNSELING?

15:42.593 --> 15:43.768
-WE DIDN'T FIGHT,

15:45.118 --> 15:46.684
JUST STARTED TALKING LESS AND
LESS UNTIL WE GOT TO THE POINT

15:46.815 --> 15:48.382
WHERE THERE'S NOTHING
LEFT TO TALK ABOUT.

15:50.688 --> 15:51.907
SO, I FIGURED I'D
COME BACK HERE

15:52.038 --> 15:53.604
AND TRY SOME
PRO BONO WORK,

15:54.562 --> 15:55.955
AND SEE IF I COULD
MAKE SENSE OUT OF IT.

15:57.478 --> 15:58.783
-IS THERE ANOTHER, UH--

15:58.914 --> 15:59.784
-I DON'T KNOW.

16:03.832 --> 16:05.268
I THINK ABOUT IT,
I GO NUTS.

16:08.793 --> 16:11.231
WHEN YOU AND GAYLE
SPLIT UP, DID, UH--

16:11.361 --> 16:13.929
-SAME, I WENT NUTS.

16:16.976 --> 16:18.325
-I THINK I SEE HER IN
EVERY RED CONVERTIBLE

16:18.455 --> 16:20.022
THAT GOES DOWN THE STREET.

16:20.153 --> 16:21.893
I HEAR HER VOICE, I TURN
AND I LOOK, SHE'S NOT THERE.

16:22.024 --> 16:23.504
I HEAR A SONG, IT
REMINDS ME OF HER.

16:25.071 --> 16:28.204
-MITCH: "OUR HOUSE,"
CROSBY, STILLS AND NASH.

16:28.335 --> 16:29.771
THAT WAS OUR SONG.

16:31.468 --> 16:34.080
EVERY TIME I HEARD THAT,
I'D THINK OF GAYLE AND, UH,

16:35.820 --> 16:37.257
I STILL DO.

16:38.127 --> 16:39.999
CRAIG, I DON'T KNOW
WHAT TO TELL YOU.

16:42.479 --> 16:44.264
YOU JUST GOTTA
GIVE IT SOME TIME.

16:45.961 --> 16:46.918
-HOW MUCH?

16:48.746 --> 16:50.444
-AS MUCH AS IT TAKES.

16:52.098 --> 16:53.012
-GREAT.

16:55.144 --> 16:56.406
[OPENS BEER]

17:05.807 --> 17:07.765
-[UPBEAT MUSIC]

17:22.301 --> 17:24.173
-DJ: WHO'S NEXT
TO CHALLENGE KYLA?

17:25.782 --> 17:27.481
ALL RIGHT, YOU,
GET OUTTA HERE.

17:29.265 --> 17:30.353
-NO WAY.

17:33.095 --> 17:35.228
1200 BUCKS, I COULD
USE THAT KINDA CASH.

17:35.358 --> 17:36.925
-I KNOW, MAN, YOU
SHOULD GO FOR IT.

17:37.056 --> 17:38.013
-YOU CAN TOTALLY DO IT.

17:38.144 --> 17:38.927
-YOU THINK?

17:39.058 --> 17:39.841
-AW, DEFINITELY.

17:39.971 --> 17:40.842
-EASILY.

17:41.582 --> 17:43.062
-COME ON, GO
FOR IT, BABY.

17:46.152 --> 17:47.327
-HOBIE, WHAT ARE
YOU DOING HERE?

17:47.457 --> 17:49.242
-I'M HERE TO
WIN THE 1200.

17:49.372 --> 17:51.766
LET'S GO! YEAH!

17:51.896 --> 17:53.855
-LET'S GO, HOBIE!
COME ON, DO IT!

17:53.985 --> 17:54.812
COME ON, MAN!

17:54.943 --> 17:59.513
-[LIVELY DANCE MUSIC]

19:01.923 --> 19:05.187
-[CROWD CHEERS]

19:05.318 --> 19:06.275
-HE WON!

19:06.406 --> 19:09.017
-[CROWD CHEERS AND APPLAUDS]

19:09.800 --> 19:11.237
-HEY, YOU DIDN'T
LET ME WIN, DID YOU?

19:11.367 --> 19:13.848
-NO, YOU WERE REALLY
GOOD, CONGRATULATIONS.

19:14.718 --> 19:15.458
-WHOA, THANKS.

19:15.589 --> 19:16.851
YEAH!

19:19.462 --> 19:21.377
-[CLUB MUSIC PLAYS]

19:21.508 --> 19:22.335
ALL RIGHT!

19:25.947 --> 19:27.688
-CONGRATULATIONS, YOU DID
WHAT NO ONE ELSE COULD.

19:27.818 --> 19:29.342
YOU WON THE
$1200 PRIZE MONEY.

19:29.472 --> 19:30.995
-ALL RIGHT!

19:37.219 --> 19:39.830
-ALL RIGHT, SHOW ME SOME
ID AND THE MONEY'S YOURS.

19:39.961 --> 19:42.093
-UH, I SHOWED IT TO
THE GUY AT THE DOOR.

19:42.224 --> 19:44.313
-YOU SHOWED HIM; NOW,
YOU GOTTA SHOW ME.

19:46.663 --> 19:48.752
-YEAH.

19:57.065 --> 20:00.982
-[DARK MUSIC]

20:08.337 --> 20:11.471
-TWELVE HUNDRED BUCKS, I WON
AND THEY WON'T GIVE IT TO ME.

20:11.601 --> 20:14.735
-YEAH, BUT YOU BROKE THE RULES
WHEN YOU USED THE FAKE ID.

20:16.519 --> 20:17.912
YOU GOT KIND OF
A BART SIMPSON

20:18.042 --> 20:19.522
FINGER-IN-THE-SOCKET
THING GOING THERE, HUH?

20:19.653 --> 20:21.524
-COME ON, CRAIG,
I'M SERIOUS!

20:21.655 --> 20:23.961
WHAT DOES AGE HAVE TO DO
WITH A DANCE COMPETITION?

20:24.092 --> 20:26.877
I WAS THE BEST DANCER.
I SHOULD GET THE MONEY.

20:27.008 --> 20:28.009
-BUT YOU
MISREPRESENTED YOURSELF

20:28.139 --> 20:29.402
TO GET INTO
THE CONTEST.

20:29.532 --> 20:31.230
-WE SHOULD TAKE
THIS TO COURT.
-WE?

20:31.360 --> 20:32.709
-YOU'RE MY LAWYER.

20:32.840 --> 20:34.233
-THERE'S A PRECEDENT
GOING AGAINST YOU.

20:34.363 --> 20:35.799
A TEENAGER IN LAS VEGAS.

20:35.930 --> 20:37.540
HE WON A WHOLE BUNCH
OF MONEY IN THE SLOTS,

20:37.671 --> 20:39.063
BUT HE WASN'T 21.
THEY DIDN'T GIVE
HIM THE MONEY.

20:39.760 --> 20:41.152
-I SAY WE GO FOR IT.

20:41.283 --> 20:43.503
WHAT DO YOU SAY? WILL
YOU BE MY LAWYER?

20:44.939 --> 20:46.027
-I'LL LOOK INTO IT.

20:46.157 --> 20:47.724
-ALL RIGHT, GOOD.

20:47.855 --> 20:48.682
-HEY, HOBIE.

20:48.812 --> 20:49.683
-YEAH.

20:50.553 --> 20:51.641
-DOES YOUR DAD
KNOW WHAT HAPPENED?

20:52.686 --> 20:55.297
-UH, NO, AND YOU
CAN'T TELL HIM.

20:55.906 --> 20:57.256
ATTORNEY-CLIENT
CONFIDENTIALITY.

20:57.386 --> 20:58.431
-OH, THAT'S NOT FAIR.

20:58.561 --> 21:00.563
-I KNOW. IT'S THE LAW.

21:03.218 --> 21:04.132
-[DOOR CLOSES]

21:05.133 --> 21:07.701
-LIFEGUARD: PLEASE STAND
BACK BEHIND THE YELLOW LINE.

21:11.966 --> 21:14.316
-HE STILL SAYS HE WON'T LEAVE
'TIL HIS LAWYER GETS BACK.

21:15.665 --> 21:17.580
-THE ATTORNEY'S ON THE WAY
FROM THE COURTHOUSE NOW.

21:17.711 --> 21:19.060
-I DON'T THINK
IT'LL MATTER.

21:19.539 --> 21:20.888
AS UNFEELING AS
IT MIGHT SEEM,

21:21.018 --> 21:23.194
YOUR UNCLE IS TRESPASSING
ON COUNTY LAND.

21:23.978 --> 21:26.154
NOW, WE DON'T WANT
A FREAK SHOW HERE.

21:26.285 --> 21:27.634
IT'S ALREADY BEEN
ON THE NEWS,

21:27.764 --> 21:28.939
AND IT'S GIVEN THE
COUNTY A BLACK EYE.

21:29.070 --> 21:30.114
-WELL, YOU'RE
GONNA HAVE TO

21:30.245 --> 21:31.246
PICK HIM UP AND
CARRY HIM AWAY.

21:33.683 --> 21:34.858
-DON'T LOOK AT ME.

21:35.468 --> 21:36.295
LOOK AT HIM.

21:37.296 --> 21:39.080
-MR. TULLY, MR. POMEROY.

21:39.210 --> 21:41.822
CRAIG IS EYES THAT SEE
AT NIGHT'S ATTORNEY.

21:42.475 --> 21:44.085
-THIS IS A COURT ORDER TO
ALLOW EYES THAT SEE AT NIGHT

21:44.215 --> 21:46.305
TO REMAIN WHERE HE IS UNTIL
THERE'S A FINAL DECISION

21:46.435 --> 21:47.654
ON THE LAND LEASE ISSUE.

21:47.784 --> 21:49.351
-LAND LEASE?

21:49.482 --> 21:52.789
-YEAH, THIS LEASE IS
BETWEEN THE ORIGINAL OWNERS

21:52.920 --> 21:56.967
OF THIS BEACH, CHUMASH INDIANS
AND THE SPANISH SETTLERS.

21:57.098 --> 21:58.534
-I CAN'T READ THIS.

21:58.665 --> 22:01.145
-I KNOW, I CAN'T
EITHER, BUT THEY CAN.

22:01.668 --> 22:03.191
IT WAS HANDED DOWN IN
THEIR FAMILY FOR 300 YEARS.

22:03.322 --> 22:05.236
-WHAT IN THE WORLD
HAS THIS GOT TO DO

22:05.367 --> 22:06.673
WITH COUNTY
BEACH JURISDICTION?

22:06.803 --> 22:08.457
-THE COUNTY BOUGHT THE
BEACH FROM THE SPANISH,

22:08.588 --> 22:09.806
BUT THE SPANISH NEVER
HAD THE RIGHT TO SELL IT

22:09.937 --> 22:11.330
BECAUSE THEY
ONLY HAD A LEASE,

22:11.460 --> 22:13.157
AND THAT LEASE EXPIRED A
LITTLE OVER A YEAR AGO,

22:13.288 --> 22:15.116
SO I'M AFRAID THIS
BEACH HAS REVERTED

22:15.246 --> 22:18.293
TO ITS ORIGINAL OWNERS,
THE CHUMASH INDIANS.

22:21.427 --> 22:22.776
-BUCHANNON, DO SOMETHING.

22:24.386 --> 22:25.256
-WHAT?

22:26.867 --> 22:29.435
HE COULD THROW US OFF HIS
BEACH FOR TRESPASSING.

22:44.188 --> 22:45.929
-MITCH: COME ON,
TAKE A RECHECK.

22:46.060 --> 22:48.192
-CRAIG: NAH, I'M NOT
LIFEGUARD MATERIAL ANY MORE.

22:48.323 --> 22:49.672
-MITCH: SURE YOU ARE.

22:49.803 --> 22:50.586
-CRAIG: YOU'RE NOT
SURE ABOUT ANYTHING.

22:50.717 --> 22:52.414
-MITCH: SURE, I AM.

22:52.545 --> 22:53.850
-CRAIG: OH, REALLY? WHAT
ABOUT EYES THAT SEE AT NIGHT?

22:53.981 --> 22:55.156
YOU SURE YOU'RE DOING
THE RIGHT THING?

22:55.286 --> 22:57.854
-MITCH: WELL,
MAYBE, YEAH.

22:57.985 --> 22:58.855
I DON'T KNOW.

22:59.508 --> 23:00.335
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

23:00.466 --> 23:02.598
-YEAH! I THINK.

23:02.729 --> 23:04.252
-YEAH, RIGHT, NEITHER
ONE OF US ARE SURE

23:04.383 --> 23:05.819
AND I'LL TELL YOU WHY.

23:06.472 --> 23:07.951
BECAUSE IT GOES AGAINST
EVERYTHING A LIFEGUARD

23:08.082 --> 23:09.344
IS TRAINED TO DO.

23:09.475 --> 23:10.954
-HE SIGNED PAPERS
IN THE HOSPITAL.

23:11.085 --> 23:12.695
HE'S ALREADY REFUSED ALL
EXTRAORDINARY MEASURES

23:12.826 --> 23:14.175
TO SAVE HIS LIFE.

23:14.305 --> 23:15.916
HE'S WILLING HIMSELF
TO DIE RIGHT NOW.

23:16.046 --> 23:19.136
WE'RE NOT CHOOSING
WHEN. HE IS!

23:19.267 --> 23:20.834
WE'RE JUST HELPING
HIM CHOOSE WHERE!

23:21.965 --> 23:23.706
-NO, NO, NO,
NO, NO, NO,

23:23.837 --> 23:26.143
WHAT YOU'RE DOING IS YOU'RE
PUTTING A SPIN ON THIS THING

23:26.274 --> 23:27.449
TO EASE YOUR CONSCIENCE!

23:27.580 --> 23:28.972
-WHAT'S THAT
SUPPOSED TO MEAN?

23:29.103 --> 23:30.974
-MEANING WHEN IS NOT
OKAY, BUT WHERE IS!

23:31.105 --> 23:32.193
-OKAY, SO I DON'T
KNOW HOW I FEEL!

23:32.323 --> 23:33.368
YOU DON'T HAVE TO YELL!

23:33.499 --> 23:35.152
-I'M NOT YELLING, I'M...

23:39.026 --> 23:40.549
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

23:40.680 --> 23:44.858
IT'S JUST THAT THIS
WHOLE THING IS CONFUSING.

23:44.988 --> 23:46.250
-HOW THE HELL DO
YOU THINK I FEEL?

23:46.381 --> 23:47.556
-I DON'T KNOW!

23:47.687 --> 23:51.821
-ALL RIGHT, I FEEL
LIKE IT'S RIGHT.

23:54.607 --> 23:55.434
HOW DO YOU FEEL?

23:56.130 --> 23:58.132
-I'VE NEVER HAD TO DEAL
WITH THIS SITUATION.

23:59.046 --> 24:00.090
I DON'T KNOW.

24:04.530 --> 24:06.445
-SYMPTOMS,
RESPIRATORY DISTRESS,

24:06.575 --> 24:08.838
ABDOMINAL CRAMPS
AND VOMITING.

24:11.493 --> 24:12.363
NEELY.

24:13.582 --> 24:14.409
-HMM?

24:15.541 --> 24:16.846
-COME ON, YOU'RE
GONNA HAVE TO PASS

24:16.977 --> 24:18.761
THIS FIRST-AID TEST
TO MAKE RECHECK.

24:19.588 --> 24:22.112
OKAY, LISTEN.
RESPIRATORY DISTRESS,

24:22.243 --> 24:24.071
ABDOMINAL CRAMPS
AND VOMITING.

24:24.201 --> 24:25.159
WHAT COULD CAUSE THIS?

24:26.900 --> 24:28.379
-ANAPHYLACTIC SHOCK,

24:29.468 --> 24:33.167
POSSIBLY AN ADVERSE
REACTION TO BEE STINGS?

24:33.994 --> 24:34.864
-RIGHT.

24:36.518 --> 24:39.086
YOU KNOW, RECHECK REQUIRES
A PHYSICAL, NEELY,

24:39.739 --> 24:40.914
AND A BLOOD TEST.

24:52.534 --> 24:54.884
-[TRIBAL MUSIC]

25:08.594 --> 25:10.247
-I'LL TAKE THE
BLAME FOR THE FIRE.

25:10.378 --> 25:11.945
IT'S CEREMONIAL

25:12.075 --> 25:14.034
I JUST DIDN'T HAVE THE HEART
TO MAKE HIM PUT IT OUT.

25:14.164 --> 25:15.426
-DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.

25:19.692 --> 25:22.390
-ALL RIGHT, TWO THINGS.
ONE, ON THE BEACH--

25:22.521 --> 25:25.132
-THE ANCIENT WAYS
HAVE TO BE HONORED.

25:28.135 --> 25:31.486
YOU AND YOUR FRIEND,
YOU UNDERSTAND THIS.

25:32.356 --> 25:33.619
-I THINK WE DO.

25:33.749 --> 25:35.446
-BY RESPECTING MY DEATH,

25:35.577 --> 25:38.014
YOU HAVE SHOWN THAT YOU
HAVE RESPECTED MY LIFE.

25:38.145 --> 25:41.365
-I RESPECT YOU,
BUT I'M A LIFEGUARD,

25:41.496 --> 25:43.193
AND YOU'VE GOTTA
RESPECT ME, TOO.

25:43.324 --> 25:44.978
MY JOB IS TO SAVE LIVES.

25:45.108 --> 25:46.936
-I UNDERSTAND.

25:47.067 --> 25:51.158
WHEN I DO WHAT I HAVE TO DO,
YOU DO WHAT YOU HAVE TO DO.

25:56.076 --> 25:57.991
MY SPIRIT WILL
LEAVE MY BODY,

25:58.121 --> 26:00.733
AND FLY ON THE WINGS OF
AN EAGLE TO THE STARS.

26:43.079 --> 26:46.909
-[MAN SPEAKS
NATIVE AMERICAN LANGUAGE]

26:50.347 --> 26:54.700
-[DRUMS BEAT]

26:59.748 --> 27:02.664
-[TRIBAL CHANTING AND MUSIC]

28:34.756 --> 28:37.977
-I JUST, LOOK, I DON'T
KNOW IF IT'S BURNOUT,

28:38.717 --> 28:40.588
OR I'M JUST SICK OF BEING
ON THE A-LIST TO PARTIES.

28:40.719 --> 28:43.460
I JUST KNOW THAT IT'S GOTTA BE
ABOUT SOMETHING OTHER THAN--

28:45.593 --> 28:47.421
IT'S ABOUT DOING SOMETHING
THAT FEELS RIGHT.

28:48.944 --> 28:50.032
I UNDERSTAND.

28:51.686 --> 28:52.948
I UNDERSTAND,
RIGHT, GINA.

28:54.167 --> 28:55.603
I'LL CALL YOU BACK
ABOUT 8:00 YOUR TIME.

28:56.386 --> 28:58.824
-GRANDMA WILL GET US SOME
POPCORN, OKAY, SWEETIE?

28:58.954 --> 28:59.781
OKAY.

29:09.922 --> 29:10.749
-YEAH.

29:17.103 --> 29:18.713
YEAH, LOOK, I'LL
CALL YOU TOMORROW.

29:18.844 --> 29:19.975
I GOTTA GO. BYE.

29:21.716 --> 29:23.849
-HEY! HEY!

29:25.241 --> 29:26.286
HEY, KID!

29:28.288 --> 29:29.550
DON'T STEP UP THERE!

29:29.680 --> 29:31.030
HEY! HOLD IT!

29:32.422 --> 29:33.946
HOLD ON! HEY, HEY!

29:37.688 --> 29:41.170
HEY! NO!

29:41.301 --> 29:43.303
-[GRANDMA SCREAMS]

29:43.433 --> 29:45.087
-[BOY SCREAMS]

29:49.439 --> 29:54.444
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

30:04.019 --> 30:07.544
-[GRANDMA CRIES
AND SCREAMS]

30:41.927 --> 30:43.798
-[CROWD CHATTERS]

30:53.025 --> 30:54.113
-THERE, RIGHT THERE.

31:13.610 --> 31:14.873
-[BOY COUGHS]

31:15.003 --> 31:16.831
-IT'S OKAY, BUD,
YOU'LL BE ALL RIGHT NOW.

31:16.962 --> 31:17.832
YOU'RE SAFE NOW.

31:19.181 --> 31:20.704
GOOD BOY, GOOD BOY.

31:21.401 --> 31:23.882
YOU'LL BE ALL RIGHT.
IT'S ALL GONNA BE OKAY.

31:24.012 --> 31:26.232
-[SOFT MUSIC]

31:34.022 --> 31:36.024
-HEY, RECHECK,
BIG DAY, HUH?

31:36.155 --> 31:37.460
-YEAH, SO THEY SAY.

31:37.591 --> 31:38.897
-YOU'RE TAKING IT,
AREN'T YOU?

31:41.073 --> 31:42.204
-I DON'T THINK SO.

31:43.771 --> 31:44.641
-NEELY!

31:46.078 --> 31:47.470
NEELY!

31:47.601 --> 31:49.559
YOU CAN'T BE A LIFEGUARD
UNTIL YOU PASS RECHECK.

31:49.690 --> 31:50.647
-YES, I CAN.

31:50.778 --> 31:51.692
-NO, YOU CAN'T!

31:51.822 --> 31:53.389
THE BEACH CLUB IS HIRING.

31:53.520 --> 31:55.304
A PRIVATE CLUB ISN'T SO
PICKY ABOUT ITS LIFEGUARDS.

31:55.435 --> 31:57.002
-PICKY? WHAT ARE
YOU TALKING ABOUT?

31:57.132 --> 31:58.394
-I'M NOT IN GOOD
ENOUGH SHAPE, ALL RIGHT?

31:58.525 --> 31:59.656
-YES, YOU ARE!

31:59.787 --> 32:01.223
-NO, MY BACK,
IT'S NOT READY.

32:01.354 --> 32:03.182
-NO, NO, THIS ISN'T
ABOUT YOUR BACK, NEELY.

32:03.312 --> 32:05.140
-HOW DO YOU KNOW
WHAT IT'S ABOUT?

32:05.749 --> 32:06.750
-I KNOW.

32:06.881 --> 32:08.361
-YOU DON'T KNOW ANYTHING.

32:09.057 --> 32:09.928
NO ONE DOES.

32:13.279 --> 32:15.716
-[SOMBER MUSIC]

32:17.979 --> 32:19.720
-GIVE THIS TO MICHAEL,
WILL YOU? THANKS.

32:19.850 --> 32:21.113
-IS IT TRUE ABOUT NEELY?

32:21.765 --> 32:23.115
-YEAH, I'M AFRAID SO.

32:23.245 --> 32:24.507
-WITHOUT HER, HOW
MANY CANDIDATES DO

32:24.638 --> 32:26.074
WE HAVE FOR RECHECK?

32:26.205 --> 32:31.079
-LET'S SEE, ONE, TWO,
THREE, FOUR, FIVE--

32:31.210 --> 32:32.124
-SIX.

32:33.516 --> 32:35.388
-[MITCH LAUGHS]

32:36.998 --> 32:39.827
SO, WHAT MADE YOU CHANGE
YOUR MIND, PRAY TELL?

32:39.958 --> 32:41.829
-I THINK IT WAS THE SOUND
OF A YOUNG KID CRYING.

32:43.396 --> 32:44.397
-I READ THE REPORT.

32:45.528 --> 32:48.749
ALL RIGHT, LET'S SEE IF YOU'RE
STILL LIFEGUARD MATERIAL.

33:00.979 --> 33:01.936
-WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

33:02.067 --> 33:03.155
-I THOUGHT YOU QUIT.

33:03.285 --> 33:04.678
-I CAME TO CLEAR
OUT MY LOCKER,

33:04.808 --> 33:06.201
BUT I SEE YOU'RE
DOING IT FOR ME.

33:07.028 --> 33:08.116
-IS THIS WHY YOU QUIT?

33:08.247 --> 33:09.770
-GIVE ME THOSE!

33:09.900 --> 33:11.337
-DONNA: YOU KNOW, THIS
EXPLAINS EVERYTHING, NEELY.

33:11.990 --> 33:14.079
HITTING ON CRAIG,
KNOCKING OVER GLASSES.

33:14.731 --> 33:16.081
YOU WEREN'T GETTING
MAKE-UP IN THAT PHARMACY.

33:16.211 --> 33:17.299
YOU WERE GETTING THOSE.

33:17.430 --> 33:18.735
-THIS IS NONE OF
YOUR BUSINESS.

33:19.954 --> 33:21.303
-YOU'RE ADDICTED, NEELY!

33:21.434 --> 33:22.783
-I'M NOT ADDICTED.

33:22.913 --> 33:23.958
-THEN THROW THOSE AWAY.

33:25.916 --> 33:28.441
-YOU DON'T KNOW WHAT I'M
GOING THROUGH, HOW I--

33:28.571 --> 33:29.920
-YES, I DO, I DO!

33:30.051 --> 33:32.140
MY SISTER WAS HOOKED
ON PAIN PILLS.

33:32.880 --> 33:34.316
YOU'RE ON THE EDGE
OF A CLIFF, NEELY.

33:34.925 --> 33:37.145
EITHER BACK AWAY OR
THOSE WILL PUSH YOU OFF.

33:38.364 --> 33:39.539
LET ME HELP YOU.

33:39.669 --> 33:40.757
GIVE ME THE PILLS.

33:43.804 --> 33:47.677
-[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC]

33:53.074 --> 33:56.164
-[SIGHS] I CAN'T!

34:02.344 --> 34:03.954
-[GRUNTING]

34:07.610 --> 34:08.610
-LOOK AT WHAT
YOU'VE DONE!

34:17.446 --> 34:19.447
-DONNA: WHEN YOU'RE
READY FOR HELP, CALL ME.

34:20.145 --> 34:21.188
I'M HERE FOR YOU, NEELY.

34:33.027 --> 34:36.248
-RECHECK! [BLOWS WHISTLE]

34:36.378 --> 34:39.599
-[DRAMATIC MUSIC]

34:48.737 --> 34:49.956
-WOO HOO!

35:18.420 --> 35:20.509
[MITCH APPLAUDS]

35:34.741 --> 35:37.787
-[LAUGHS] ALL
RIGHT, YOU MADE IT.

35:37.918 --> 35:39.049
CONGRATULATIONS.

35:39.920 --> 35:40.877
HERE, CHECK THIS OUT.

35:41.704 --> 35:42.792
SEE IF THIS FITS.

35:42.923 --> 35:45.273
YEAH, IT LOOKS
GOOD, ALL RIGHT!

35:46.013 --> 35:46.883
-THANKS.

35:48.146 --> 35:49.364
-MITCH: I'M PROUD
OF YOU, MAN.

36:01.333 --> 36:02.551
-LIFEGUARD: BEHIND
THE LINE, PLEASE!

36:03.552 --> 36:05.075
CAN WE GET YOU
BEHIND THE YELLOW LINE?

36:07.469 --> 36:12.082
-[CROWD CHATTERS]

36:31.928 --> 36:33.103
-YOU'RE ON, COUNSELOR.

36:36.803 --> 36:39.153
-THE LAND LEASE CHALLENGING
THE COUNTY'S JURISDICTION

36:39.284 --> 36:41.024
OVER THIS BEACH HAS BEEN
THOROUGHLY INVESTIGATED

36:41.155 --> 36:42.939
BY SUPERIOR COURT
JUDGE ALICE FRANKLIN.

36:43.070 --> 36:45.551
ITS VALIDITY HAS BEEN
OVERRULED AND THROWN OUT.

36:47.117 --> 36:49.207
THE CIRCUS IS
OVER. I'M SORRY.

36:49.337 --> 36:50.686
WE GOTTA CLAIM
THIS BEACH.

36:50.817 --> 36:52.253
-TULLY, YOU AND I
KNOW THAT THIS ISN'T

36:52.384 --> 36:53.733
ABOUT THE
COUNTY'S RIGHTS.

36:53.863 --> 36:55.082
IT'S NOT ABOUT NATIVE
AMERICAN RIGHTS.

36:56.214 --> 36:58.216
IT'S ABOUT A HUMAN BEING'S
RIGHT TO DIE THE WAY HE WANTS,

36:59.695 --> 37:00.522
WITH DIGNITY.

37:01.480 --> 37:03.569
-PLEASE RESPECT MY
UNCLE AND HIS WISHES.

37:03.699 --> 37:05.135
-LIKE I SAID, I'M SORRY.

37:05.266 --> 37:06.398
I CAN'T LET HIM STAY HERE.

37:06.528 --> 37:09.096
-[TRIBAL MUSIC]

37:09.227 --> 37:12.142
-[NATIVE AMERICAN SINGING]

37:56.926 --> 37:59.451
-[NATIVE AMERICAN
FAMILY CHEERS]

38:03.193 --> 38:05.457
-YOU ALL TAKE CHARGE!
GET AN AMBULANCE!

38:15.336 --> 38:16.468
-NO PULSE, NO BREATHING.

38:17.425 --> 38:19.340
-EYES THAT SEE AT NIGHT:
WHEN I DO WHAT I HAVE TO DO,

38:19.471 --> 38:21.473
YOU DO WHAT
YOU HAVE TO DO.

38:24.476 --> 38:25.825
-BEGIN CPR.

38:25.955 --> 38:27.653
-NO, PLEASE, HE DOESN'T
WANT EXTREME MEASURES.

38:27.783 --> 38:28.654
-I HAVE TO DO THIS.

